<paragraph blockId="57.[151,558,583,609]" box="[151,558,583,609]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,558,583,609]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,558,583,609]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Benson, 1945" authorityName="Benson" authorityYear="1945" box="[226,558,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Neurotomini">
Neurotomini 
<bibRefCitation author="Benson, R. B." box="[393,558,583,609]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="25 - 33" refId="ref72962" refString="Benson, R. B. (1945) Classification of the Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera Symphyta). Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London, Series B, Taxonomy, 14 (3 - 4), 25 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1945. tb 00012. x" type="journal article" year="1945">Benson, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,655,970]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
The representatives of this tribe are characterized as follows (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[836,1034,655,681]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
): head with lateral sutures divergent forward and not connected with antennal furrows (
<figureCitation box="[718,787,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1614,1638]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,918,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-342@37.[151,1436,918,1590]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 1. Key to tribes and genera 1" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876495/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
: 1a); tarsal claws elongate (e.g., 
<figureCitation box="[1154,1254,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="110.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-26@110.[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="110" captionText="FIGURE 21. Neurotoma coreana, female, Korea – (a) dorsally, (b) lateroventrally, (c) head &amp; thorax dorsally, (d) head &amp; thorax ventrolaterally, (e) face, (f) antenna, (g) sawsheath laterally, (h) claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876544/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 21h</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1265,1309,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="112.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-26@112.[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="112" captionText="FIGURE 23. Neurotoma iridescens, female, Russia – (a) dorsally, (b) lateroventrally, (c) head &amp; thorax dorsally, (d) head &amp; thorax ventrolaterally, (e) face, (f) antenna, (g) sawsheath laterally, (h) claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876548/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">23h</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1321,1366,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="113.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-19@113.[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="113" captionText="FIGURE 24. Neurotoma iridescens, female, Japan – (a) dorsally, (b) lateroventrally, (c) head &amp; thorax dorsally, (d) head &amp; thorax ventrolaterally, (e) face, (f) antenna, (g) sawsheath laterally, (h) claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876552/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">24h</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1377,1424,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="115.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@115.[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURE 26. Neurotoma satoi, female, Korea (paratype) – (a) dorsally, (b) lateroventrally, (c) head &amp; thorax dorsally, (d) head &amp; thorax ventrolaterally, (e) face, (f) antenna, (g) sawsheath laterally, (h) claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876556" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876556/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">26h</figureCitation>
); forewing with vein Scl absent (
<figureCitation box="[497,564,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1614,1638]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,918,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-342@37.[151,1436,918,1590]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 1. Key to tribes and genera 1" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876495/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
: 1b); abdominal sternum 
<quantity box="[848,890,727,754]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
female not strongly convex, with paired rounded ridges apically, enclosing rather small triangular marginal depression (fig. 4E–G in 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1095,1291,763,789]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
); lancet with lamnium enlarged (
<figureCitation box="[369,437,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1614,1638]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,918,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-342@37.[151,1436,918,1590]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 1. Key to tribes and genera 1" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876495/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
: 1c).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,655,970]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
Two postulated autapomorphies, the absence of vein Scl in the forewing and the enlarged lamnium of the lancet of the ovipositor, may support the monophyly of this tribe. In our molecular analyses using COI and NaK sequences (
<figureCitation box="[159,288,907,934]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–16" captionStartId="97.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[294,1293,186,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@97.[279,1307,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="97" captionText="FIGURES 14–16: 14. Hypothesized relationships based on adult morphology in Pamphiliinae for several genera and species groups of Pamphilius (modified from Shinohara 2002b, only genera and species groups with molecular data are included). 15. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences. 16. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876530/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 15, 16</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[309,434,908,933]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[309,434,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Neurotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also retrieved as monophyletic with 100% UFBoot support.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,655,970]" box="[199,1027,943,970]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benson" authorityYear="1945" box="[250,393,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Neurotomini">Neurotomini</taxonomicName>
contains a single genus, 
<emphasis box="[673,805,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName box="[673,801,944,969]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Neurotoma</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
in the extant fauna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
